SAVAGERY.name: Savagery
SAVAGERY.flavorText: It is true that some druids are savage, but others still enjoy a quiet moment and a spot of tea.

PERPETUAL FLAME.name: Perpetual Flame
PERPETUAL FLAME.flavorText: Flame is perpetual.* *Perpetual only applies to current turn.

FROTHING BERSERKER.name: Frothing Berserker
FROTHING BERSERKER.flavorText: He used to work as an accountant before he tried his hand at Berserkering.

NEERU FIREBLADE.name: Neeru Fireblade
NEERU FIREBLADE.flavorText: Look at this guy! He’s obviously evil! OBVIOUSLY!!!

PARTNER ASSIGNMENT.name: Partner Assignment
PARTNER ASSIGNMENT.flavorText: In every group assignment, someone does all the legwork.

WAR GOLEM.name: War Golem
WAR GOLEM.flavorText: Golems are not afraid, but for some reason they still run when you cast Fear on them. Instinct, maybe? A desire to blend in?

KOR'KRON ELITE.name: Kor'kron Elite
KOR'KRON ELITE.flavorText: The Kor'kron are the elite forces of Garrosh Hellscream. Let's just say you don't want to run into these guys while wearing a blue tabard.

ORNERY DIREHORN.name: Ornery Direhorn
ORNERY DIREHORN.flavorText: "It's an herbivore. How dangerous can it be?" - Famous last words

DUSKFALLEN AVIANA.name: Duskfallen Aviana
DUSKFALLEN AVIANA.flavorText: Someone called her "Tweety". She didn't take it well.

CORPSICLE.name: Corpsicle
CORPSICLE.flavorText: Comes in three tasty flavors: Gross, Disgusting, and Chocolate!

SAVORY DEVIATE DELIGHT.name: Savory Deviate Delight
SAVORY DEVIATE DELIGHT.flavorText: "Savory" is a creative way to put it.

CRYSTALSMITH KANGOR.name: Crystalsmith Kangor
CRYSTALSMITH KANGOR.flavorText: He wants to tank, but Boom always makes him play support.

EVISCERATE.name: Eviscerate
EVISCERATE.flavorText: There is a high cost to Eviscerating your opponent. You might tweak your elbow! That really hurts!

PRIZE PLUNDERER.name: Prize Plunderer
PRIZE PLUNDERER.flavorText: But he'll never be able to plunder the prize of a happy childhood.

TOXMONGER.name: Toxmonger
TOXMONGER.flavorText: Not all spiders are born poisonous. That's where he comes in.

GLUTTONOUS OOZE.name: Gluttonous Ooze
GLUTTONOUS OOZE.flavorText: Three time winner of the Un'Goro weapon eating contest.

CAREFREE COOKIE.name: Carefree Cookie
CAREFREE COOKIE.flavorText: Moisturized, unbothered, and in his cauldron.

MIND VISION.name: Mind Vision
MIND VISION.flavorText: I see what you did there.

VARDEN DAWNGRASP.name: Varden Dawngrasp
VARDEN DAWNGRASP.flavorText: Varden Dawngrasp could wield fire, summon hailstorms, and morph a night elf into a sheep with a snap of their fingers. Knowing how malleable reality could be, certain labels felt downright trivial.

MAESTRA OF THE MASQUERADE.name: Maestra of the Masquerade
MAESTRA OF THE MASQUERADE.flavorText: She doesn't drop character until after the DVD commentary.

SPIRIT JAILER.name: Spirit Jailer
SPIRIT JAILER.flavorText: "Sure, they're in your deck, but the mind is like, the REAL prison."

URSATRON.name: Ursatron
URSATRON.flavorText: It's been programmed to include all the bear necessities.

OMEN.name: Omen
OMEN.flavorText: His tremendous wisdom could not survive the foul influence of the demons’ fel magic during the War of the Ancients. But his blessing from Elune did.

STRANGLETHORN HEART.name: Stranglethorn Heart
STRANGLETHORN HEART.flavorText: The Stranglethorn mentality is to be happy with the bare necessities.

VANESSA VANCLEEF.name: Vanessa VanCleef
VANESSA VANCLEEF.flavorText: Some people collect stamps or flowers. She collects enemies.

SMALL-TIME BUCCANEER.name: Small-Time Buccaneer
SMALL-TIME BUCCANEER.flavorText: "Oh, I'm not serious about it. I only pirate on the weekends."

TAVISH STORMPIKE.name: Tavish Stormpike
TAVISH STORMPIKE.flavorText: "Hurry up, laddie, we're getting overrun! Serpents everywhere! They may look cute, but do ye see the fury in their eyes?!" —Tavish Stormpike

EXPLOSIVE RUNES.name: Explosive Runes
EXPLOSIVE RUNES.flavorText: Sometimes it's safer NOT to read the warning signs.

AWAKENING TREMORS.name: Awakening Tremors
AWAKENING TREMORS.flavorText: A rude followup to the Sleepy Tremors.

MENAGERIE WARDEN.name: Menagerie Warden
MENAGERIE WARDEN.flavorText: Please? Can I keep him? I promise to clean his cage every day.

XB-488 DISPOSALBOT.name: XB-488 Disposalbot
XB-488 DISPOSALBOT.flavorText: You'll be so surprised when you figure out what XB stands for.

ANCIENT SHIELDBEARER.name: Ancient Shieldbearer
ANCIENT SHIELDBEARER.flavorText: Back in her day, each shield weighed two tons and she had to carry four of them on each arm!

WILDHEART GUFF.name: Wildheart Guff
WILDHEART GUFF.flavorText: Guff faced his biggest challenge yet: making friends on a battlefield.

IVUS, THE FOREST LORD.name: Ivus, the Forest Lord
IVUS, THE FOREST LORD.flavorText: He's always welcome at the local tavern, unlike a certain Ancient.

LIGHTNING BOLT.name: Lightning Bolt
LIGHTNING BOLT.flavorText: Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt!

SECURITY AUTOMATON.name: Security Automaton
SECURITY AUTOMATON.flavorText: Honestly, I feel less secure when it's around.

LADY PRESTOR.name: Lady Prestor
LADY PRESTOR.flavorText: To her credit, the best bodyguard for the king WOULD be a dragon in disguise.

QUEEN OF PAIN.name: Queen of Pain
QUEEN OF PAIN.flavorText: Her sister is the Queen of Pane who sells windows and shower doors.

MENAGERIE MUG.name: Menagerie Mug
MENAGERIE MUG.flavorText: He's a chip off the old jug.

VOLATILE SKELETON.name: Volatile Skeleton
VOLATILE SKELETON.flavorText: These ice sculpures look so realistic!

JAZZ BASS.name: Jazz Bass
JAZZ BASS.flavorText: No birds, plural, were harmed in the making of this bass.

ELISE STARSEEKER.name: Elise Starseeker
ELISE STARSEEKER.flavorText: A large part of her job entails not mixing up the Map to the Golden Monkey with the Map to Monkey Island.

BARKSKIN.name: Barkskin
BARKSKIN.flavorText: Make like a tree… and gain armor.

THE 8 HANDS FROM BEYOND.name: The 8 Hands From Beyond
THE 8 HANDS FROM BEYOND.flavorText: It was a one-eyed, eight-handed, giant purple planet eater.

PLAGUE OF MADNESS.name: Plague of Madness
PLAGUE OF MADNESS.flavorText: Don't bring a candle to a knife fight.

GLAIVETAR.name: Glaivetar
GLAIVETAR.flavorText: Might need tuning, I think it's a bit sharp.

RADIANCE OF AZSHARA.name: Radiance of Azshara
RADIANCE OF AZSHARA.flavorText: Uses Arcane, Fire, and Frost magic to vanquish Queen Azshara's foes. And for her skincare routine!

OPEN THE WAYGATE.name: Open the Waygate
OPEN THE WAYGATE.flavorText: Although powerful, the incantation is simple. It’s just a jump to the left, and then a step to the right.

SHUDDERBLOCK.name: Shudderblock
SHUDDERBLOCK.flavorText: Beware the hinges that pinch, the scales that splinter!

RANCOR.name: Rancor
RANCOR.flavorText: Wise men say "Only fools rush in." Wise Orcs say the opposite.

LIGHTWARDEN.name: Lightwarden
LIGHTWARDEN.flavorText: She’s smaller than her sisters Mediumwarden and Heavywarden.

KIRIN TOR MAGE.name: Kirin Tor Mage
KIRIN TOR MAGE.flavorText: The Kirin Tor reside in the floating city of Dalaran. How do you make a Dalaran float? Two scoops of ice cream, one scoop of Dalaran.

SUSPICIOUS PIRATE.name: Suspicious Pirate
SUSPICIOUS PIRATE.flavorText: EVERY party should be a costume party.

STONEHILL DEFENDER.name: Stonehill Defender
STONEHILL DEFENDER.flavorText: Briefly tried stand-up comedy under the name "Stonehill Offender", but turtles are just too thin-skinned.

PICK POCKET.name: Pick Pocket
PICK POCKET.flavorText: He'll pick anyone's pocket, except a gnome's. He'd never stoop so low.

POLYMORPH.name: Polymorph
POLYMORPH.flavorText: There was going to be a pun in this flavor text, but it just came out baa-d.

DEVILSAUR EGG.name: Devilsaur Egg
DEVILSAUR EGG.flavorText: A key ingredient in all discerning Funnel Cake recipes.

ARCANE EXPLOSION.name: Arcane Explosion
ARCANE EXPLOSION.flavorText: This spell is much better than Arcane Implosion.

SPLENDIFEROUS WHIZBANG.name: Splendiferous Whizbang
SPLENDIFEROUS WHIZBANG.flavorText: After his work at Boomsday Labs, he's taken what Dr. Boom taught him and applied it to the most important inventions of all - TOYS!!!

ARGENT WATCHMAN.name: Argent Watchman
ARGENT WATCHMAN.flavorText: Who argent watches the Argent Watchman?

voicelines.play: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/6/6a/VO_AT_109_PLAY_01.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_109_PLAY_01.wav
voicelines.attack: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/a/a4/VO_AT_109_ATTACK_02.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_109_ATTACK_02.wav I saw that.
voicelines.death: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/3/3a/VO_AT_109_DEATH_03.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_109_DEATH_03.wav <death sound>

AZSHARAN SENTINEL.name: Azsharan Sentinel
AZSHARAN SENTINEL.flavorText: For some, the Sundering was the collapse of civilization. For others, it was a great core workout.

HOUNDMASTER.name: Houndmaster
HOUNDMASTER.flavorText: "Who let the dogs out?" he asks. It's rhetorical.

EYE OF THE STORM.name: Eye of the Storm
EYE OF THE STORM.flavorText: If that's the eye, I would hate to see the rest of the storm.

MELOMANIA.name: Melomania
MELOMANIA.flavorText: I once saw a horse that had watermelons for hair. It was a melon mane, ya?!

SHIP'S CHIRURGEON.name: Ship's Chirurgeon
SHIP'S CHIRURGEON.flavorText: Knows the answer to every medical question except how to pronounce his name.

EVOLVE.name: Evolve
EVOLVE.flavorText: So you say you want an evolution. Well, you know. We all want to change the board.

REVENANT RASCAL.name: Revenant Rascal
REVENANT RASCAL.flavorText: Turns out his face really did get stuck that way.

LOREWALKER CHO.name: Lorewalker Cho
LOREWALKER CHO.flavorText: Lorewalker Cho archives and shares tales from the land of Pandaria, but his favorite story is the one where Joey and Phoebe go on a road trip.

voicelines.play: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/e/e8/VO_Tutorial06_CHO_02_03.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_Tutorial06_CHO_02_03.wav

FLARE.name: Flare
FLARE.flavorText: Not only does it reveal your enemies, but it's also great for parties!

ARTANIS.name: Artanis
ARTANIS.flavorText: Artanis will forge a new future for the protoss, even if it means destroying everything they ever knew.

SHADEHOUND.name: Shadehound
SHADEHOUND.flavorText: This Shadehound wasn't just a good boy. He was the best.

WARSONG WRANGLER.name: Warsong Wrangler
WARSONG WRANGLER.flavorText: "Me? Playing favorites? I love my beasts all the same!"

TRANSMOGRIFIER.name: Transmogrifier
TRANSMOGRIFIER.flavorText: All it takes is some imagination and a cardboard box.

SHAKY ZIPGUNNER.name: Shaky Zipgunner
SHAKY ZIPGUNNER.flavorText: The Grimy Goons can get you any weapon you want but if you want it to not explode you gotta pay extra.

MONSTROUS MOSQUITO.name: Monstrous Mosquito
MONSTROUS MOSQUITO.flavorText: I know every creature is valuable in the ecosystem of life. But these guys SUCK.

RAMKAHEN WILDTAMER.name: Ramkahen Wildtamer
RAMKAHEN WILDTAMER.flavorText: She gets to decide what cards go to the Hall of Fame.

GOBOGLIDE TECH.name: Goboglide Tech
GOBOGLIDE TECH.flavorText: The word "glide" is always in quotes in the manual.

DARKTHORN QUILTER.name: Darkthorn Quilter
DARKTHORN QUILTER.flavorText: Still mad about not being let into the spiders' sewing club.

BRRRLOC.name: Brrrloc
BRRRLOC.flavorText: He may be frozen fish, but he fights fresh!

TEMPLE ENFORCER.name: Temple Enforcer
TEMPLE ENFORCER.flavorText: He also moonlights Thursday nights as a bouncer at the Pig and Whistle Tavern.

BLOODSAIL CULTIST.name: Bloodsail Cultist
BLOODSAIL CULTIST.flavorText: They're really just in it for the Blood Parrot.

BAIT AND SWITCH.name: Bait and Switch
BAIT AND SWITCH.flavorText: Oh my god, the bait and switch works every time!

HIGH PRIESTESS JEKLIK.name: High Priestess Jeklik
HIGH PRIESTESS JEKLIK.flavorText: If you love Jeklik, set her free. YOU CAN'T GET RID OF HER.

SKYVATEER.name: Skyvateer
SKYVATEER.flavorText: When you go without fruits in an airship, you get a nasty case of skyvy.

GOLDSHIRE FOOTMAN.name: Goldshire Footman
GOLDSHIRE FOOTMAN.flavorText: If 1/2 minions are all that is defending Goldshire, you would think it would have been overrun years ago.

SIPHON SOUL.name: Siphon Soul
SIPHON SOUL.flavorText: You probably should avoid siphoning your own soul. You might create some kind of weird infinite loop.

ILLIDAN'S GIFT.name: Illidan's Gift
ILLIDAN'S GIFT.flavorText: "This gift's burden will always be yours to bear... I lost the receipt." -Illidan

DEFIAS RINGLEADER.name: Defias Ringleader
DEFIAS RINGLEADER.flavorText: He stole the deed to town years ago, so technically the town is his. He just calls people Scrub to be mean.

SHOULDER CHECK.name: Shoulder Check
SHOULDER CHECK.flavorText: One... two... yeah, all present and correct.

TROGG GLOOMEATER.name: Trogg Gloomeater
TROGG GLOOMEATER.flavorText: His breath smells like agony and despair, which is still better than most troggs.

MANA WYRM.name: Mana Wyrm
MANA WYRM.flavorText: These wyrms feed on arcane energies, and while they are generally considered a nuisance rather than a real threat, you really shouldn't leave them alone with a bucket of mana.

SOUTHSEA SQUIDFACE.name: Southsea Squidface
SOUTHSEA SQUIDFACE.flavorText: Quick! Before I drown! Let me sharpen your sword for you.

MARK OF Y'SHAARJ.name: Mark of Y'Shaarj
MARK OF Y'SHAARJ.flavorText: Y'Shaarj had three sons: Mark, Theodore, and Chris.

TOXICOLOGIST.name: Toxicologist
TOXICOLOGIST.flavorText: Double-majoring in culinary sciences was definitely a mistake.

STOCKADES GUARD.name: Stockades Guard
STOCKADES GUARD.flavorText: "You there! Defend this prison with your life. It's my break."

STOCKADES PRISONER.name: Stockades Prisoner
STOCKADES PRISONER.flavorText: She was arrested for lockpicking. Her imprisonment was not well thought out.

JADE DISPLAY.name: Jade Display
JADE DISPLAY.flavorText: The Jade Lotus just releases the same product every year but with an upgraded camera.

AIRLOCK BREACH.name: Airlock Breach
AIRLOCK BREACH.flavorText: Open the pod bay doors, Maladaar.

THE MARSH QUEEN.name: The Marsh Queen
THE MARSH QUEEN.flavorText: Question: What's scarier, one giant angry dinosaur or 20 smaller vicious ones? Answer: AHHHHHHH THEY FOUND MEEEEEE

MOUNTAIN GIANT.name: Mountain Giant
MOUNTAIN GIANT.flavorText: His mother said that he was just big boned.

WARSONG ENVOY.name: Warsong Envoy
WARSONG ENVOY.flavorText: "What do you mean we didn’t give the flag to the Druid?"

CANDLE BREATH.name: Candle Breath
CANDLE BREATH.flavorText: "And Waxadred shall light their fires, with roaring breath hotter than pyres! Come before him, scamp and vandal, pledge your faith and lift your candle!"

ZEPHRYS THE GREAT.name: Zephrys the Great
ZEPHRYS THE GREAT.flavorText: "Of course it's perfect, you're just not seeing how to use it."

GENERAL VEZAX.name: General Vezax
GENERAL VEZAX.flavorText: Contrast this with Specific Vezax, who only gets resummoned if you have exactly 4 Armor.

DARK PACT.name: Dark Pact
DARK PACT.flavorText: "Don't worry about the fine print. Just sign here."

ICE FISHING.name: Ice Fishing
ICE FISHING.flavorText: Glow fish, war fish... blow fish, more fish...

POCKET DIMENSION.name: Pocket Dimension
POCKET DIMENSION.flavorText: On average, this gets you around 3 cards. And none of them have Overload.

voicelines.attack: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/7/7d/VO_TTN_931_Male_Anubisath_Play_01.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_TTN_931_Male_Anubisath_Play_01.wav You will not come closer!

DARK CONVICTION.name: Dark Conviction
DARK CONVICTION.flavorText: In his court, Uther is judge, jury, AND executioner…

YSIEL WINDSINGER.name: Ysiel Windsinger
YSIEL WINDSINGER.flavorText: Reach down into your lungs. The wind that resides there is your greatest treasure. It provides the gift of song, which is free. *But not less than (1)

ALLOY ADVISOR.name: Alloy Advisor
ALLOY ADVISOR.flavorText: Numbers may betray you, but steel... steel you can trust.

KING PHAORIS.name: King Phaoris
KING PHAORIS.flavorText: When you're the king of the cats, the whole desert is your litterbox.

SYNTHESIZE.name: Synthesize
SYNTHESIZE.flavorText: After the invention of elemental audio processing, Azeroth went through a major synth phase.

DREADPRISON GLAIVE.name: Dreadprison Glaive
DREADPRISON GLAIVE.flavorText: Keep your allies close. Keep your evil demons in your weapon.

PIRANHA POACHER.name: Piranha Poacher
PIRANHA POACHER.flavorText: This snack certainly isn’t smiling back…

DEADLY SHOT.name: Deadly Shot
DEADLY SHOT.flavorText: Our ballista operator is effective, but not picky.

GOODY TWO-SHIELDS.name: Goody Two-Shields
GOODY TWO-SHIELDS.flavorText: These are my shields. There are at least two like them, and both are mine.

THE BLACK KNIGHT.name: The Black Knight
THE BLACK KNIGHT.flavorText: He was sent by the Lich King to disrupt the Argent Tournament. We can pretty much mark that a failure.

SUNWALKER.name: Sunwalker
SUNWALKER.flavorText: She doesn’t ACTUALLY walk on the Sun. It's just a name. Don’t worry!

ARCANE DEVOURER.name: Arcane Devourer
ARCANE DEVOURER.flavorText: Likes her magic with a pinch of salt.

BOLSTER.name: Bolster
BOLSTER.flavorText: The best offense is a good defense.

MEKGINEER THERMAPLUGG.name: Mekgineer Thermaplugg
MEKGINEER THERMAPLUGG.flavorText: He was obsessed with explosives until he discovered knitting. Now he yells, “SWEATERS! MORE SWEATERS!”

FLEETHOOF PEARLTUSK.name: Fleethoof Pearltusk
FLEETHOOF PEARLTUSK.flavorText: Guest interactions may vary over the duration of the visit.

FELSTALKER.name: Felstalker
FELSTALKER.flavorText: This puppy chews up cards instead of shoes.

LINEDANCE PARTNER.name: Linedance Partner
LINEDANCE PARTNER.flavorText: Where did you come from? (Linedance Partner's Battlecry) Where did you go? (Face)

EXARCH MALADAAR.name: Exarch Maladaar
EXARCH MALADAAR.flavorText: The Auchenai order was founded to preserve the memory of Draenei that have passed. But why stop at remembrance when they can live once more?

SHADOW BOLT.name: Shadow Bolt
SHADOW BOLT.flavorText: It’s a Bolt. It's made out of Shadow. What more do you need to know!

ZERGLING.name: Zergling
ZERGLING.flavorText: It's all fun and games until 8 of these show up at your door at the 2 minute mark.

CRACKLING RAZORMAW.name: Crackling Razormaw
CRACKLING RAZORMAW.flavorText: Wasn't clever enough to go AROUND the electric fence.

CLEAVE.name: Cleave
CLEAVE.flavorText: Hey you two…could you stand next to each other for a second…

MIDNIGHT WOLF.name: Midnight Wolf
MIDNIGHT WOLF.flavorText: Three of these would make for an EPIC T-shirt.

THORNGROWTH SENTRIES.name: Thorngrowth Sentries
THORNGROWTH SENTRIES.flavorText: Maybe we shouldn't drink from this Oasis…

MOK'NATHAL LION.name: Mok'Nathal Lion
MOK'NATHAL LION.flavorText: Never underestimate a lioness when her pride is on the line.

DARKSHIRE ALCHEMIST.name: Darkshire Alchemist
DARKSHIRE ALCHEMIST.flavorText: The secret ingredient: liquified funnel cake.

TENTACLE GRIP.name: Tentacle Grip
TENTACLE GRIP.flavorText: "WINTER VEIL WAS MONTHS AGO, WHY ARE YOUR LIGHTS STILL UP?"

BLAZING POWER.name: Blazing Power
BLAZING POWER.flavorText: Apply heat directly to the damaged area.

SHADOW WORD: RUIN.name: Shadow Word: Ruin
SHADOW WORD: RUIN.flavorText: Discovered by a worgen priest after a giant spilled a drink on her new white robes.

GORLOC RAVAGER.name: Gorloc Ravager
GORLOC RAVAGER.flavorText: Be careful what you fish for.

BOLF RAMSHIELD.name: Bolf Ramshield
BOLF RAMSHIELD.flavorText: Bolf keeps coming in 2nd at the Grand Tournament. It might be his year this year, if Lebron doesn't enter.

voicelines.attack: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/4/43/VO_AT_124_ATTACK_04.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_124_ATTACK_04.wav Who's next?!
voicelines.death: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/f/f2/VO_AT_124_DEATH_05.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_124_DEATH_05.wav <death sound>

BLADE FLURRY.name: Blade Flurry
BLADE FLURRY.flavorText: "Look, it's not just about waving daggers around really fast. It's a lot more complicated than that." - Shan, Rogue Trainer

MIRROR ENTITY.name: Mirror Entity
MIRROR ENTITY.flavorText: "You go first." - Krush'gor the Behemoth, to his pet boar.

SPIRIT OF THE BAT.name: Spirit of the Bat
SPIRIT OF THE BAT.flavorText: Nah nah nah nah, nah nah nah nah, nah nah nah nah, nah nah nah nah

TWISTED KNOWLEDGE.name: Twisted Knowledge
TWISTED KNOWLEDGE.flavorText: People eat eight spiders in their sleep per year. Centaurs have two rib cages. Dwarves are just counterfeit titans.

KALDOREI PRIESTESS.name: Kaldorei Priestess
KALDOREI PRIESTESS.flavorText: Elune, I implore you... bless my game with good rng, so that I may achieve Legend with a 100% winrate.

ARCANE OVERFLOW.name: Arcane Overflow
ARCANE OVERFLOW.flavorText: On this ship, when you can’t use an int, learn how to float.

HYDROLOGIST.name: Hydrologist
HYDROLOGIST.flavorText: Murloc hydrologists are pretty rare. Most murloc undergrads pick computer science.

BLOOD GUARD.name: Blood Guard
BLOOD GUARD.flavorText: Has never donated blood and doesn’t plan on ever doing so.

SINDRAGOSA.name: Sindragosa
SINDRAGOSA.flavorText: "I recognize your effort but I think your magic still has room for improvement." - Sindragosa after taking a class on giving constructive feedback.

GALAKROND, THE WRETCHED.name: Galakrond, the Wretched
GALAKROND, THE WRETCHED.flavorText: Fel-flames slowly writhed around the skeleton, until the great bones knit themselves together into a demonic monstrosity. Rafaam shielded his face from the heat but could not hide his grin.

HEADHUNT.name: Headhunt
HEADHUNT.flavorText: Even though the red lenses blurred his vision and greatly inhibited his ability to make out color and detail, he looked cool as heck.

DWARF PLANET.name: Dwarf Planet
DWARF PLANET.flavorText: Hey, who let Magni Bronzebeard, who we all know is famous for his Magni Touch, land on this planet!?

N'ZOTH, GOD OF THE DEEP.name: N'Zoth, God of the Deep
N'ZOTH, GOD OF THE DEEP.flavorText: It really just wants to cuddle all the creatures of Azeroth.

TEAR REALITY.name: Tear Reality
TEAR REALITY.flavorText: One time it gave me a black flower, a smiling pot, and a foil first edition Dracthyr.

SWEET TOOTH.name: Sweet Tooth
SWEET TOOTH.flavorText: He's been eyeballing that ice cream cone all day!

METAMORFIN.name: Metamorfin
METAMORFIN.flavorText: Always wanted to be the green ranger.

CABAL ACOLYTE.name: Cabal Acolyte
CABAL ACOLYTE.flavorText: How did he get to the top of his class? He pulled a few strings!

POISONED BLADE.name: Poisoned Blade
POISONED BLADE.flavorText: How much more poisoned can a blade get? The answer is a lot. A lot more poisoned.

TWILIGHT MEDIUM.name: Twilight Medium
TWILIGHT MEDIUM.flavorText: This twilight is too dark. And this twilight is too bright. But THIS twilight is juuuuuuuuust right!

ZILLIAX DELUXE 3000.name: Zilliax Deluxe 3000
ZILLIAX DELUXE 3000.flavorText: It only took us 2998 prototypes to figure out how to make the perfect card... by having YOU do it!

REMOTE CONTROL.name: Remote Control
REMOTE CONTROL.flavorText: For some reason, my dog keeps trying to eat this.

BESTIAL MADNESS.name: Bestial Madness
BESTIAL MADNESS.flavorText: "Hey this isn't what we were trying to excavate!"

CRYSTAL MERCHANT.name: Crystal Merchant
CRYSTAL MERCHANT.flavorText: I won't ask about your mana curve if you don't ask where I got these.

SEWER CRAWLER.name: Sewer Crawler
SEWER CRAWLER.flavorText: His clothing is "ratty" in more ways than one.

GRIMOIRE OF SACRIFICE.name: Grimoire of Sacrifice
GRIMOIRE OF SACRIFICE.flavorText: "What kind of bedtime story is this?"

APOTHECARY'S CARAVAN.name: Apothecary's Caravan
APOTHECARY'S CARAVAN.flavorText: If you won't bring out your dead, we'll bring the dead to you.

CORROSIVE SLUDGE.name: Corrosive Sludge
CORROSIVE SLUDGE.flavorText: The result of centuries of terrible sanitation.

RAZORGLAIVE SENTINEL.name: Razorglaive Sentinel
RAZORGLAIVE SENTINEL.flavorText: For the worgen that has everything: more claws.

voicelines.death: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/a/af/VO_ONY_036_Female_Worgen_Attack_01.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_ONY_036_Female_Worgen_Attack_01.wav Death from above!

ROBES OF PROTECTION.name: Robes of Protection
ROBES OF PROTECTION.flavorText: Warning: Robes of Protection are intended for targeted effects only and are not an effective defense against Flamestrike, Twisting Nether, or other AOE attacks.

MORTAL STRIKE.name: Mortal Strike
MORTAL STRIKE.flavorText: "If you only use one ability, use Mortal Strike." - The Warrior Code, Line 6

FEL SUMMONER.name: Fel Summoner
FEL SUMMONER.flavorText: All's well that ends fel when the fel summoner summons well.

KOBOLD LIBRARIAN.name: Kobold Librarian
KOBOLD LIBRARIAN.flavorText: Kobolds sort books using a gooey decimal system.

DRAGONCASTER.name: Dragoncaster
DRAGONCASTER.flavorText: It’s challenging to perform magic on dragonback. It’s so easy to drop the rabbit.

AVENGING WRATH.name: Avenging Wrath
AVENGING WRATH.flavorText: Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham!

SING-ALONG BUDDY.name: Sing-Along Buddy
SING-ALONG BUDDY.flavorText: One of the buttons makes you sound JUST like Ragnaros. BY FIRE BE HEARD!

SPECTRAL PILLAGER.name: Spectral Pillager
SPECTRAL PILLAGER.flavorText: It turns out you CAN take it with you.

SHADOW MADNESS.name: Shadow Madness
SHADOW MADNESS.flavorText: You can rationalize it all you want, it's still a mean thing to do.

YSERA.name: Ysera
YSERA.flavorText: Ysera rules the Emerald Dream. Which is some kind of green-mirror-version of the real world, or something?

SARONITE SHAMBLER.name: Saronite Shambler
SARONITE SHAMBLER.flavorText: They play the best rock music at the saro-nite club.

CLONING DEVICE.name: Cloning Device
CLONING DEVICE.flavorText: Zerek got sick of fighting over the remote.

ARCHWITCH WILLOW.name: Archwitch Willow
ARCHWITCH WILLOW.flavorText: One of the demons will do all the work while the other gets the same grade.

HIGH NOON DUELIST.name: High Noon Duelist
HIGH NOON DUELIST.flavorText: "My ultimate is rea- ah, errr, I mean, I have enough Mana."

GRAL, THE SHARK.name: Gral, the Shark
GRAL, THE SHARK.flavorText: “… We’re gonna need a bigger board.”

WISPERING WOODS.name: Wispering Woods
WISPERING WOODS.flavorText: We didn't actually fire the guy who named Dark Wispers.

SERPENT WARD.name: Serpent Ward
SERPENT WARD.flavorText: When snakes get sick, they get sent to the Serpent Ward.

CHILLFALLEN BARON.name: Chillfallen Baron
CHILLFALLEN BARON.flavorText: He hates when people call 60 degree weather cold.

BRANCHING PATHS.name: Branching Paths
BRANCHING PATHS.flavorText: Three paths diverged in a darkened hall, and I – I took the one less traveled by, And got eaten by a slime.

PSYCHIC CONJURER.name: Psychic Conjurer
PSYCHIC CONJURER.flavorText: "I see... a WISP? Why do you have a wisp?!"

NATALIE SELINE.name: Natalie Seline
NATALIE SELINE.flavorText: She discovered Xal'atath, Blade of the Black Empire, a terrible weapon of shadow magic that could both swallow a soul and cut a mean julienne.

SPELLBREAKER.name: Spellbreaker
SPELLBREAKER.flavorText: Spellbreakers can rip enchantments from magic-wielders. The process is painless and can be performed on an outpatient basis.

WRETCHED EXILE.name: Wretched Exile
WRETCHED EXILE.flavorText: If you're cold, they're cold. Let your wretches inside.

MIRE KEEPER.name: Mire Keeper
MIRE KEEPER.flavorText: "Hey.... Is that Mire for sale?" "No. I'm keeping it."

BLIZZARD.name: Blizzard
BLIZZARD.flavorText: This spell can be very Entertaining.

BARONESS VASHJ.name: Baroness Vashj
BARONESS VASHJ.flavorText: Vashj was supposed to make an appearance in "The Sunken City," but after a freak accident in "Ashes of Outland," she ended up here.

CRESCENDO.name: Crescendo
CRESCENDO.flavorText: The more you flail your arms, the better the orchestra plays! Yup, that's definitely how it works.

BANANA BUFFOON.name: Banana Buffoon
BANANA BUFFOON.flavorText: You could say he has a certain appeal.

VENOMOUS SCORPID.name: Venomous Scorpid
VENOMOUS SCORPID.flavorText: Despite what Guff says, he is NOT a "nice little guy."

CORPSETAKER.name: Corpsetaker
CORPSETAKER.flavorText: Her extensive collection of corpses includes one of nearly every type. She'd love for you to join it.

SPAWN OF DEATHWING.name: Spawn of Deathwing
SPAWN OF DEATHWING.flavorText: Aww, who’s the most dangerous threat to the world? You are!

SOUTHSEA SCOUNDREL.name: Southsea Scoundrel
SOUTHSEA SCOUNDREL.flavorText: "…and here we see the Southsea Scoundrel in their natural habitat: a den of scum and villainy."

SILENCE.name: Silence
SILENCE.flavorText: Reserved for enemy spellcasters, evil liches from beyond the grave, and karaoke nights at the Grim Guzzler.

UNLEASH THE HOUNDS.name: Unleash the Hounds
UNLEASH THE HOUNDS.flavorText: You must read the name of this card out loud each time you play it.

ELDRITCH BEING.name: Eldritch Being
ELDRITCH BEING.flavorText: Tor flud huth respa di blarry? Fleebletor glomdor!

LORD JARAXXUS.name: Lord Jaraxxus
LORD JARAXXUS.flavorText: "TRIFLING GNOME! YOUR ARROGANCE WILL BE YOUR UNDOING!!!!"

SABRETOOTH STALKER.name: Sabretooth Stalker
SABRETOOTH STALKER.flavorText: It's gotten a bit long in the tooth.

FILLETFIGHTER.name: Filletfighter
FILLETFIGHTER.flavorText: "What do you mean this isn't the meal you asked for? ! I made you a Fillet Minion!"

SACRIFICIAL SUMMONER.name: Sacrificial Summoner
SACRIFICIAL SUMMONER.flavorText: Summoning will cost you an arm and a brother.

SWAMP DRAGON EGG.name: Swamp Dragon Egg
SWAMP DRAGON EGG.flavorText: Would you eat them in a ditch? Would you eat them with a witch?

BRANN BRONZEBEARD.name: Brann Bronzebeard
BRANN BRONZEBEARD.flavorText: Contains 75% more fiber than his brother Magni!

ADAPTIVE AMALGAM.name: Adaptive Amalgam
ADAPTIVE AMALGAM.flavorText: We've only explored 5% of the ocean. So there's like a 95% chance this is accurate.

BENEVOLENT BANKER.name: Benevolent Banker
BENEVOLENT BANKER.flavorText: "Oh no, you've got me confused. I'm Ben, the evil ent banker. I only work with evil trees!"

BOGSHAPER.name: Bogshaper
BOGSHAPER.flavorText: The tricky part is getting them to HOLD their shape.

METAL DETECTOR.name: Metal Detector
METAL DETECTOR.flavorText: Weirdly still works on Sand Coins.

ELEMENTAL ALLIES.name: Elemental Allies
ELEMENTAL ALLIES.flavorText: Reno’s lucky he wasn’t caught by a fire elemental.

MISSILE POD.name: Missile Pod
MISSILE POD.flavorText: Welcome to the Missile Pod, your one-stop shop for all things missile-related. Tune in each week for developments in the world of missiles.

TOTEM GOLEM.name: Totem Golem
TOTEM GOLEM.flavorText: What happens when you glue a buncha totems together.

POWER OVERWHELMING.name: Power Overwhelming
POWER OVERWHELMING.flavorText: We cannot even describe how horrible the death is. It's CRAZY bad! Maybe worse than that. Just don't do it.

ENCHANTED CAULDRON.name: Enchanted Cauldron
ENCHANTED CAULDRON.flavorText: Do you smell what the cauldron is cooking? If so, we apologize.

AYA BLACKPAW.name: Aya Blackpaw
AYA BLACKPAW.flavorText: Though young, Aya took over as the leader of Jade Lotus through her charisma and strategic acumen when her predecessor was accidentally crushed by a jade golem.

SCARLET CRUSADER.name: Scarlet Crusader
SCARLET CRUSADER.flavorText: Never wash your whites with a Scarlet Crusader.

TOUCH OF THE NATHREZIM.name: Touch of the Nathrezim
TOUCH OF THE NATHREZIM.flavorText: "You're giving your soul to me? I'm touched."

DESPERATE STAND.name: Desperate Stand
DESPERATE STAND.flavorText: They're grateful for the help, but most minions would prefer not dying in the first place.

ROTFACE.name: Rotface
ROTFACE.flavorText: Daddy! I think I made a Legendary!

KRONX DRAGONHOOF.name: Kronx Dragonhoof
KRONX DRAGONHOOF.flavorText: The only one who knows how to properly prepare Galakrond's coffee.

SPIRIT OF THE DEAD.name: Spirit of the Dead
SPIRIT OF THE DEAD.flavorText: Just because you’re dead doesn’t mean you’re off the team.

DRACONIC STUDIES.name: Draconic Studies
DRACONIC STUDIES.flavorText: Our Draconic Studies program has a high rate of burnout.

FAN THE HAMMER.name: Fan the Hammer
FAN THE HAMMER.flavorText: I thought Kurtrus was more of a fan of glaives.

JUMPSCARE!.name: Jumpscare!
JUMPSCARE!.flavorText: Might need a pair of [Druidic Pants of Water Resistance] after this one.

YOUTHFUL BREWMASTER.name: Youthful Brewmaster
YOUTHFUL BREWMASTER.flavorText: His youthful enthusiasm doesn’t always equal excellence in his brews. Don’t drink the Mogu Stout!

UNDERCITY HUCKSTER.name: Undercity Huckster
UNDERCITY HUCKSTER.flavorText: Psst! Wanna buy a random class card (from your opponent's class)?

SPRING THE TRAP.name: Spring the Trap
SPRING THE TRAP.flavorText: Talk about starting off on the wrong foot.

CHO'GALL.name: Cho'gall
CHO'GALL.flavorText: Even after all this time, Gul'dan still makes Cho'gall go get donuts and coffee.

ARCANE BRILLIANCE.name: Arcane Brilliance
ARCANE BRILLIANCE.flavorText: They could probably do with a dash of Arcane Humility.

IMPRISONED GAN'ARG.name: Imprisoned Gan'arg
IMPRISONED GAN'ARG.flavorText: Factory Direct Fiery War Axe. Please allow two turns for delivery.

PRISMATIC JEWEL KIT.name: Prismatic Jewel Kit
PRISMATIC JEWEL KIT.flavorText: The divine trick to jewelcrafting is tumbling your own rocks.

TOKI, TIME-TINKER.name: Toki, Time-Tinker
TOKI, TIME-TINKER.flavorText: Just a twist to the left, one quarter turn to the right and … oops! Well, we didn’t need that timeline anyway.

KOBOLD GEOMANCER.name: Kobold Geomancer
KOBOLD GEOMANCER.flavorText: In the old days, Kobolds were the finest candle merchants in the land. Then they got pushed too far...

VIOLET TEACHER.name: Violet Teacher
VIOLET TEACHER.flavorText: If you don't pay attention, you may be turned into a pig. And then you get your name on the board.

PLANTED EVIDENCE.name: Planted Evidence
PLANTED EVIDENCE.flavorText: So you're telling me this wasn't Natural Causes?

IGNEOUS ELEMENTAL.name: Igneous Elemental
IGNEOUS ELEMENTAL.flavorText: We wanted to name him "Ingenious Elemental", but he just wasn't that bright.

TRAM OPERATOR.name: Tram Operator
TRAM OPERATOR.flavorText: The guy in the back is screaming… because the train ride is so fun!

INVIGORATE.name: Invigorate
INVIGORATE.flavorText: No. 3 Most Internally Contentious Hearthstone Card of 2022.

DARING DRAKE.name: Daring Drake
DARING DRAKE.flavorText: First of all, how dare you? Second of all, how dare you!

IRONHIDE DIREHORN.name: Ironhide Direhorn
IRONHIDE DIREHORN.flavorText: "Boy! Bring me my masks and skull rams."

METAMORPHOSIS.name: Metamorphosis
METAMORPHOSIS.flavorText: As the humble caterpillar becomes a beautiful butterfly, so too does a demon hunter become a hideous mass of writhing destruction and unfettered chaos.

PELICAN DIVER.name: Pelican Diver
PELICAN DIVER.flavorText: The pelican’s beak is so big, some Colossal minions can even fit inside!* *This is a lie.

INFESTED GOBLIN.name: Infested Goblin
INFESTED GOBLIN.flavorText: Trust us. DON'T go cheap on the scarab repellent.

TO MY SIDE!.name: To My Side!
TO MY SIDE!.flavorText: I hunt alone. Well, me and Misha. And Huffer. And Leokk.

SI:7 AGENT.name: SI:7 Agent
SI:7 AGENT.flavorText: The agents of SI:7 are responsible for Stormwind's covert activities. Their duties include espionage, assassination, and throwing surprise birthday parties for the royal family.

OVERZEALOUS HEALER.name: Overzealous Healer
OVERZEALOUS HEALER.flavorText: In another universe, she's Genji's best friend.

ENTRAPPED SORCERESS.name: Entrapped Sorceress
ENTRAPPED SORCERESS.flavorText: "If you're a city guard, you have to tell me. Otherwise, it's entrapment."

CITY ARCHITECT.name: City Architect
CITY ARCHITECT.flavorText: "Oh, wait, I had this turned the wrong way. This was supposed to be a tower."

GIFT OF THE NAARU.name: Gift of the Naaru
GIFT OF THE NAARU.flavorText: What do I look like, a charity?

ZUL'JIN.name: Zul'jin
ZUL'JIN.flavorText: If you can dodge an axe, you can dodge a ball.

SHUDDERWOCK.name: Shudderwock
SHUDDERWOCK.flavorText: Beware the Shudderwock, my son. We're fresh out of vorpal daggers.

ARMORED WARHORSE.name: Armored Warhorse
ARMORED WARHORSE.flavorText: Yep. It's a horse... wearing armor... going to war.

DRAGONMAW OVERSEER.name: Dragonmaw Overseer
DRAGONMAW OVERSEER.flavorText: Ah, the Booterang... nothing cures peon laziness faster.

BLACKWATER BEHEMOTH.name: Blackwater Behemoth
BLACKWATER BEHEMOTH.flavorText: What's a Blackwater Behemoth's favorite meal? Fish n' Ships.

TURALYON, THE TENURED.name: Turalyon, the Tenured
TURALYON, THE TENURED.flavorText: "Let evil flee before righteousness; let the innocent live in peace. Let the day come when none need fear. For that day, I give my life gladly."

DIRE WOLF ALPHA.name: Dire Wolf Alpha
DIRE WOLF ALPHA.flavorText: We are pretty excited about the upcoming release of Dire Wolf Beta, just repost this sign for a chance at a key.

TAELAN FORDRING.name: Taelan Fordring
TAELAN FORDRING.flavorText: After growing up with the Scarlet Crusade for most of his life, Taelan finally realized they were maybe not the nicest people.

FELSCREAM BLAST.name: Felscream Blast
FELSCREAM BLAST.flavorText: All the souls start running when they see the felscream truck.

DROWN.name: Drown
DROWN.flavorText: If you play it on a Naga, they drown in their sorrows instead.

ARCANE NULLIFIER X-21.name: Arcane Nullifier X-21
ARCANE NULLIFIER X-21.flavorText: There was some hard talk between gnome magi and engineers about inventing this mech.

TINKER'S SHARPSWORD OIL.name: Tinker's Sharpsword Oil
TINKER'S SHARPSWORD OIL.flavorText: "Get ready to strike oil!" - Super-cheesy battle cry

HOWDYFIN.name: Howdyfin
HOWDYFIN.flavorText: You know who to blame if your drinking water tastes a little fishy.

TARGET DUMMY.name: Target Dummy
TARGET DUMMY.flavorText: The engineering equivalent of a "Kick Me" sticker.

TAR LURKER.name: Tar Lurker
TAR LURKER.flavorText: Hi, Tar here. Long time lurking, first time taunting…

SHIELD OF ASKARA.name: Shield of Askara
SHIELD OF ASKARA.flavorText: One can never have too many shields.

STEWART THE STEWARD.name: Stewart the Steward
STEWART THE STEWARD.flavorText: How many bites does it take to get the center of an hors d'oeuvre?

FURY (RANK 1).name: Fury (Rank 1)
FURY (RANK 1).flavorText: Rank 3 is when your mom uses your middle name.

SARUUN.name: Saruun
SARUUN.flavorText: BORN FROM THE HEAT DEATH OF COLLIDING SUPERNOVAS, SARUUN SEEKS TO INCINERATE ALL THAT WHICH REVOLVES AROUND THEM TO MERE ASHES AND STARDUST!!!! Which is pretty neato!

MEADOWSTRIDER.name: Meadowstrider
MEADOWSTRIDER.flavorText: Pwease stop meadowing in my affaiws.

GO WITH THE FLOW.name: Go with the Flow
GO WITH THE FLOW.flavorText: Just go with the flow, bro! No mo' woe fo' yo'!

HIGHLORD FORDRAGON.name: Highlord Fordragon
HIGHLORD FORDRAGON.flavorText: "Through my faith and my courage, I shall be protected. And through my honor and sacrifice, another will rise in my place."

SALOON BREWMASTER.name: Saloon Brewmaster
SALOON BREWMASTER.flavorText: Brewmaster Bru brought Barrelbrim bursting barrels of barely brewed barley brew. Barrelbrim bought Bru's barley brew, barring the barrels broken from the brazen brunch brawl.

AUDIO AMPLIFIER.name: Audio Amplifier
AUDIO AMPLIFIER.flavorText: And you thought we were putting Wildheart Guff in Core. We'd never do that! WINK WINK.

KAZAKUSAN.name: Kazakusan
KAZAKUSAN.flavorText: Kazakus had always seemed too clever a sort to bottle a brew that could do him any harm. Perhaps it should come as no surprise, then, that the originator of the Dragonfire Potion was a dragon himself.

OVERFLOW SURGER.name: Overflow Surger
OVERFLOW SURGER.flavorText: The drip on this elemental is straight fire!

LIGHTFUSED MANASABER.name: Lightfused Manasaber
LIGHTFUSED MANASABER.flavorText: Oh no, I ran out of fused Mana!

FORKED LIGHTNING.name: Forked Lightning
FORKED LIGHTNING.flavorText: If you combine it with Spooned Lightning and Knived Lightning, you have the full dining set.

voicelines.death: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/d/d8/VO_RLK_713_Female_Lich_Play_01.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_RLK_713_Female_Lich_Play_01.wav Arise, and exalt in your pure form!

CONFECTION CYCLONE.name: Confection Cyclone
CONFECTION CYCLONE.flavorText: "Oh, I thought it was a desert elemental?"

KOBOLD ILLUSIONIST.name: Kobold Illusionist
KOBOLD ILLUSIONIST.flavorText: He can make ANYTHING look like a candle.

EVASIVE WYRM.name: Evasive Wyrm
EVASIVE WYRM.flavorText: Deftly dodges spells like a real wiggle wyrm.

TOYSNATCHING GEIST.name: Toysnatching Geist
TOYSNATCHING GEIST.flavorText: So THAT'S how the Geist stole Winterveil!

TWILIGHT GEOMANCER.name: Twilight Geomancer
TWILIGHT GEOMANCER.flavorText: "Ok C'Thun, repeat after me: 'Your mother was a hamster.'"

DUSKBAT.name: Duskbat
DUSKBAT.flavorText: Happily married with two kids. It was love at first bite.

VITALITY SURGE.name: Vitality Surge
VITALITY SURGE.flavorText: If your vitality lasts longer than four hours, consult a Priest.

YREL, BEACON OF HOPE.name: Yrel, Beacon of Hope
YREL, BEACON OF HOPE.flavorText: Yrel has a lot of overdue library books.

TESS GREYMANE.name: Tess Greymane
TESS GREYMANE.flavorText: Those who cannot remember their card history are doomed to repeat it.

ROTTEN RODENT.name: Rotten Rodent
ROTTEN RODENT.flavorText: It's dead, but it's not a mouse.

KING MUKLA.name: King Mukla
KING MUKLA.flavorText: King Mukla wanders Jaguero Isle, searching for love.

CAIRNE BLOODHOOF.name: Cairne Bloodhoof
CAIRNE BLOODHOOF.flavorText: Cairne was killed by Garrosh, so... don't put this guy in a Warrior deck. It's pretty insensitive.

VENGEFUL VISAGE.name: Vengeful Visage
VENGEFUL VISAGE.flavorText: The mirror shows us nothing less than the deepest, darkest desire of our hearts: to go face.

WISHING WELL.name: Wishing Well
WISHING WELL.flavorText: Wishing upon a star? Pssshhh, that's so childish. Anyways, let me throw all my Coins into this well.

SELFLESS SIDEKICK.name: Selfless Sidekick
SELFLESS SIDEKICK.flavorText: "I got a real sense of humility from her when she bashed that quilboar's head in."

TRAVEL SECURITY.name: Travel Security
TRAVEL SECURITY.flavorText: "You're just gonna let ANY 8-Cost minion get past you!?" "...Yeah..."

C'THUN, THE SHATTERED.name: C'Thun, the Shattered
C'THUN, THE SHATTERED.flavorText: My grandfather's deck has no useless cards!

DEMENTED FROSTCALLER.name: Demented Frostcaller
DEMENTED FROSTCALLER.flavorText: He prefers that you refer to him by his nickname: 'Frostwaker.'

KERRIGAN, QUEEN OF BLADES.name: Kerrigan, Queen of Blades
KERRIGAN, QUEEN OF BLADES.flavorText: Betrayed by the terrans, she is determined to use the power of the zerg Swarm for her revenge.

KING'S DEFENDER.name: King's Defender
KING'S DEFENDER.flavorText: "King's Attacker" is a shield. Funny, huh?

RAZA THE RESEALED.name: Raza the Resealed
RAZA THE RESEALED.flavorText: The 10th anniversary edition of a classic bestseller!

WORGEN ABOMINATION.name: Worgen Abomination
WORGEN ABOMINATION.flavorText: Does anyone want to play dead!?

RUNE OF THE ARCHMAGE.name: Rune of the Archmage
RUNE OF THE ARCHMAGE.flavorText: “It’s not a slot machine! It took YEARS of rigorous studying the intricacies of the universe to unravel the strands of reality. The arcane knowledge alone would enfeeble even the most brilliant of minds. Give it the credence it deserves. It’s a magic slot machine.”

ANCHARRR.name: Ancharrr
ANCHARRR.flavorText: The problem with anchors is they often end up sinking to the bottom of your deck.

PRIEST OF THE FEAST.name: Priest of the Feast
PRIEST OF THE FEAST.flavorText: Now that's a world champion cheesecake!

KABAL OUTFITTER.name: Kabal Outfitter
KABAL OUTFITTER.flavorText: Don’t ask her for feathers on your necklace though.

SPELLSLINGER.name: Spellslinger
SPELLSLINGER.flavorText: Does he sling spells, or do his spells linger about. Who can say?

TWILIGHT DRAKE.name: Twilight Drake
TWILIGHT DRAKE.flavorText: Twilight drakes feed on Mystical Energy. And Tacos.

BONE DRAKE.name: Bone Drake
BONE DRAKE.flavorText: The bone drake brings all the dragons to the yard. He would teach you, but you have no cards.

DUSKBREAKER.name: Duskbreaker
DUSKBREAKER.flavorText: Waking up at the break of dusk is just not as impressive.

DRAGONSCALE ARMAMENTS.name: Dragonscale Armaments
DRAGONSCALE ARMAMENTS.flavorText: Why are dragons so good in the late game? 'Cause they scale!!!!

LOREKEEPER POLKELT.name: Lorekeeper Polkelt
LOREKEEPER POLKELT.flavorText: quicksort [] = [] quicksort (x:xs) = quicksort small ++ (x : quicksort large) where small = [y | y <- xs, y <= x] large = [y | y <- xs, y > x]

ROCKET AUGMERCHANT.name: Rocket Augmerchant
ROCKET AUGMERCHANT.flavorText: "Don't worry, this won't hurt me a bit."

NATURAL CAUSES.name: Natural Causes
NATURAL CAUSES.flavorText: What if the suspect was framed? What if the murder weapon was... a plant?

EMPEROR THAURISSAN.name: Emperor Thaurissan
EMPEROR THAURISSAN.flavorText: His second greatest regret is summoning an evil Firelord who enslaved his entire people.

BOG CREEPER.name: Bog Creeper
BOG CREEPER.flavorText: He's tried other things, but bog sidling, bog ambling, and bog trundling just aren't as effective as bog creeping.

PILFER.name: Pilfer
PILFER.flavorText: The class is always greener on the other side of the board.

HARVEST GOLEM.name: Harvest Golem
HARVEST GOLEM.flavorText: "Overheat threshold exceeded. System failure. Wheat clog in port two. Shutting down."

RANGARI SCOUT.name: Rangari Scout
RANGARI SCOUT.flavorText: Always takes credit for other people's discoveries.

PHALANX COMMANDER.name: Phalanx Commander
PHALANX COMMANDER.flavorText: Turns out he's really good at herding cats.

THE STONEWRIGHT.name: The Stonewright
THE STONEWRIGHT.flavorText: She wrights stone better than she reads it.

PUFFERFIST.name: Pufferfist
PUFFERFIST.flavorText: "...and then I'll hit 'em with the ol' puffercut!"

TERRIBLE CHEF.name: Terrible Chef
TERRIBLE CHEF.flavorText: Anyone can cook! But not them.

RUNEFUELED GOLEM.name: Runefueled Golem
RUNEFUELED GOLEM.flavorText: Hmm, glyph gauge is running low. Better fill up at the next town.

MISTER MUKLA.name: Mister Mukla
MISTER MUKLA.flavorText: Music is Mukla's escape from his anger. When he's on-stage, it's like he's a whole different gorilla… Until you boo him.

STARFIRE.name: Starfire
STARFIRE.flavorText: Balance is important to druids. This card is perfectly balanced.

SPREADING MADNESS.name: Spreading Madness
SPREADING MADNESS.flavorText: Most citizens of Darkshire wear those surgical masks to prevent spreading Madness to tourists.

VARIAN, KING OF STORMWIND.name: Varian, King of Stormwind
VARIAN, KING OF STORMWIND.flavorText: Man, this guy is so cool. Sure hope nothing happens to him.

OASIS SNAPJAW.name: Oasis Snapjaw
OASIS SNAPJAW.flavorText: His dreams of flying and breathing fire like his idol will never be realized.

VOID FLAYER.name: Void Flayer
VOID FLAYER.flavorText: The Void, just like onions, has flayers.

FISHY FLYER.name: Fishy Flyer
FISHY FLYER.flavorText: Like a fish out of water.

FULL-BLOWN EVIL.name: Full-Blown Evil
FULL-BLOWN EVIL.flavorText: This isn’t your average, everyday evil. This is ADVANCED evil.

UR'ZUL HORROR.name: Ur'zul Horror
UR'ZUL HORROR.flavorText: You face face face face face Jaraxxus!

REVOLVE.name: Revolve
REVOLVE.flavorText: "Please don't ride the carousel for thirty minutes after eating. After the carousel eats, I mean."

BLUEGILL WARRIOR.name: Bluegill Warrior
BLUEGILL WARRIOR.flavorText: He just wants a hug. A sloppy... slimy... hug.

THE SCARAB LORD.name: The Scarab Lord
THE SCARAB LORD.flavorText: What did it cost? 41,400 Silithid Carapace Fragments, to start.

TRIAL OF THE JORMUNGARS.name: Trial of the Jormungars
TRIAL OF THE JORMUNGARS.flavorText: The defendants were found guilty on 33 counts of wiping raid parties.

OGRE-GANG RIDER.name: Ogre-Gang Rider
OGRE-GANG RIDER.flavorText: Doesn't know his ride from his left.

VOID TERROR.name: Void Terror
VOID TERROR.flavorText: If you put this into your deck, you WILL lose the trust of your other minions.

BACKSTAB.name: Backstab
BACKSTAB.flavorText: It's funny how often yelling "Look over there!" gets your opponent to turn around.

SOUP VENDOR.name: Soup Vendor
SOUP VENDOR.flavorText: Fresh from the floor of the arena!

FOREST LORD CENARIUS.name: Forest Lord Cenarius
FOREST LORD CENARIUS.flavorText: He handpicked Malfurion, and not Illidan, to become the first druid, therefore ensuring an endless cycle of sibling rivalry.

TRIPLE SEVENS.name: Triple Sevens
TRIPLE SEVENS.flavorText: If you count the 'seven' in the name, there's actually four total 7s, not three. Huge oversight from the designers.

CAPTURED JORMUNGAR.name: Captured Jormungar
CAPTURED JORMUNGAR.flavorText: You can keep him, but you have to promise to feed him and clean out his tank every day!

STORMPIKE MARSHAL.name: Stormpike Marshal
STORMPIKE MARSHAL.flavorText: The Stormpike have a very direct take on life insurance.

FLAMETONGUE TOTEM.name: Flametongue Totem
FLAMETONGUE TOTEM.flavorText: Totemsmiths like to use the rarest woods for their totems. There are even rumors of totems made of Ironbark Protectors.

ARCANOLOGIST.name: Arcanologist
ARCANOLOGIST.flavorText: What did you draw? Shhhh… it’s a secret.

FIREWORKS TECH.name: Fireworks Tech
FIREWORKS TECH.flavorText: She learns by trial and error. Mostly error.

RESURRECT.name: Resurrect
RESURRECT.flavorText: I walked into the dungeon and noticed a slain adventurer. In his final moments, he had scrawled out a message in the dust on the wall beside him. Two words: "rez plz"

MURLOC RAIDER.name: Murloc Raider
MURLOC RAIDER.flavorText: Mrrraggglhlhghghlgh, mrgaaag blarrghlgaahahl mrgggg glhalhah a bghhll graggmgmg Garrosh mglhlhlh mrghlhlhl!!

FEL'DOREI WARBAND.name: Fel'dorei Warband
FEL'DOREI WARBAND.flavorText: "Felerin, I made you a friendship bracelet!" "...what? I said WARband, not WRISTband..."

PEASANT.name: Peasant
PEASANT.flavorText: Better pay them, or they'll join the Defias.

TIMELINE ACCELERATOR.name: Timeline Accelerator
TIMELINE ACCELERATOR.flavorText: The future is NOW! No wait, NOW!

GATTLESNAKE.name: Gattlesnake
GATTLESNAKE.flavorText: He used to be an ordinary snake until he slithered through a saloon during a brawl and walked out looking like this.

GENN GREYMANE.name: Genn Greymane
GENN GREYMANE.flavorText: Ever since Sylvanas killed his son, he's dreamed of getting… even.

GOBLIN BLASTMAGE.name: Goblin Blastmage
GOBLIN BLASTMAGE.flavorText: If you can't find a bomb to throw, just pick up any goblin invention and throw that.

UNLICENSED APOTHECARY.name: Unlicensed Apothecary
UNLICENSED APOTHECARY.flavorText: Get the ingredients wrong on ONE healing potion and they take your license. What a world!

MICRO MUMMY.name: Micro Mummy
MICRO MUMMY.flavorText: The dramatically detailed terrifically trimmed replica of the real thing!

SHADOWBOMBER.name: Shadowbomber
SHADOWBOMBER.flavorText: Shadowbomber does her job, but she's kind of phoning it in at this point.

RENEW.name: Renew
RENEW.flavorText: I am rejuvenated, I am renewed, I am my own nightlight!

CENARION HOLD.name: Cenarion Hold
CENARION HOLD.flavorText: After the War of the Shifting Sands, Cenarion Hold became a strategic outpost, awaiting the moment when the armies of C'Thun would rise once again.

YOINK!.name: Yoink!
YOINK!.flavorText: Saying the spell’s name makes it work better.

KING TOGWAGGLE.name: King Togwaggle
KING TOGWAGGLE.flavorText: Management of the Kobold Empire requires a careful balance between a lack of social services and fiscal irresponsibility.

SEAWEED STRIKE.name: Seaweed Strike
SEAWEED STRIKE.flavorText: Even as mechs, fish will still end up wrapped in seaweed.

WARP GATE.name: Warp Gate
WARP GATE.flavorText: This is gonna be really meta-warping.

FLAMESTRIKE.name: Flamestrike
FLAMESTRIKE.flavorText: When the ground is on fire, you should not stop, drop, and roll.

GLOOMSTONE GUARDIAN.name: Gloomstone Guardian
GLOOMSTONE GUARDIAN.flavorText: From the same people who brought you Choose One, and Choose Twice, comes the exciting prequel: Choose NEITHER!

CAPTAIN'S PARROT.name: Captain's Parrot
CAPTAIN'S PARROT.flavorText: Pirates and Parrots go together like Virmen and Carrots.

RAZORFEN BEASTMASTER.name: Razorfen Beastmaster
RAZORFEN BEASTMASTER.flavorText: It's a homebrew variant on my favorite role-playing game.

BONEWEB EGG.name: Boneweb Egg
BONEWEB EGG.flavorText: Noblegarden is going to be really exciting this year!

EYE OF SHADOW.name: Eye of Shadow
EYE OF SHADOW.flavorText: It's hard to makeup flavor text sometimes.

CORRIDOR SLEEPER.name: Corridor Sleeper
CORRIDOR SLEEPER.flavorText: In the workshop, I go deeper. In the mulligan, I'm a keeper. This time, I'm even cheaper. You guessed it right, I'm Corridor Sleeper.

ASPECT'S EMBRACE.name: Aspect's Embrace
ASPECT'S EMBRACE.flavorText: For when you really need a hug. Or to Imbue your Hero Power.

SAYGE, SEER OF DARKMOON.name: Sayge, Seer of Darkmoon
SAYGE, SEER OF DARKMOON.flavorText: There are no secrets between us... or refunds.

SEASCOUT OPERATOR.name: Seascout Operator
SEASCOUT OPERATOR.flavorText: The Mechafish are actually totally autonomous. We gave her a fake control pad, as a joke.

BLOODSCALP STRATEGIST.name: Bloodscalp Strategist
BLOODSCALP STRATEGIST.flavorText: “Shoot them in the face” is more of a tactic than a strategy.

RABID WORGEN.name: Rabid Worgen
RABID WORGEN.flavorText: "I'm sorry, son. We had to send Old Howler off…to a farm…to play…"

BEASTSTALKER TAVISH.name: Beaststalker Tavish
BEASTSTALKER TAVISH.flavorText: Tavish left home to forge his own path. But it still led him back to Alterac to kick some Frostwolf butt.

QUESTING ADVENTURER.name: Questing Adventurer
QUESTING ADVENTURER.flavorText: "Does anyone have some extra Boar Pelts?"

DISTRESSED KVALDIR.name: Distressed Kvaldir
DISTRESSED KVALDIR.flavorText: Oh look at that, I have been impaled.

WRATH.name: Wrath
WRATH.flavorText: The talk around the Ratchet Inn is that this card is too good and should be a Legendary.

VOIDGILL.name: Voidgill
VOIDGILL.flavorText: If you stare into the abyss, it’s said that it will stare back at you. What happens to those who’ve gazed at it their entire lives?

DOOR OF SHADOWS.name: Door of Shadows
DOOR OF SHADOWS.flavorText: Upon arrival, please ring the doorbell of shadows, and wipe your shoes on the doormat of shadows before entering.

BLOODTHISTLE ILLUSIONIST.name: Bloodthistle Illusionist
BLOODTHISTLE ILLUSIONIST.flavorText: Some people have imaginary friends. He has an imaginary twin.

ROYAL LIBRARIAN.name: Royal Librarian
ROYAL LIBRARIAN.flavorText: Books on how to flip the Auction House are down that way.

FERAL SPIRIT.name: Feral Spirit
FERAL SPIRIT.flavorText: Spirit wolves are like regular wolves with pom-poms.

SCRIBBLING STENOGRAPHER.name: Scribbling Stenographer
SCRIBBLING STENOGRAPHER.flavorText: A truly staggering 180 scribbles per minute!

NAVAL MINE.name: Naval Mine
NAVAL MINE.flavorText: A Naval Mine? I'd rather it be Naval Yours.

DIVINE SPIRIT.name: Divine Spirit
DIVINE SPIRIT.flavorText: Double the trouble. Double the fun!

SUMMONING WARD.name: Summoning Ward
SUMMONING WARD.flavorText: You couldn't handle one Snowflipper Penguin. So what hope do you have… against two?!

PARK PANTHER.name: Park Panther
PARK PANTHER.flavorText: Somebody called animal control once. It didn't work out very well for anybody.

WALNUT SPRITE.name: Walnut Sprite
WALNUT SPRITE.flavorText: How do you make a walnut laugh? Crack it up!

DISCIPLE OF GALAKROND.name: Disciple of Galakrond
DISCIPLE OF GALAKROND.flavorText: Raising Galakrond will cause thurible, thurible damage.

HOSTILE INVADER.name: Hostile Invader
HOSTILE INVADER.flavorText: "And my Axe!" "And my Axe!" "And my Axe!"

BLAZING BATTLEMAGE.name: Blazing Battlemage
BLAZING BATTLEMAGE.flavorText: Weaponized an ancient technique once used to slice cold butter.

WASTE WARDEN.name: Waste Warden
WASTE WARDEN.flavorText: Recycle that can, or you get the cuffs!

WAR CACHE.name: War Cache
WAR CACHE.flavorText: It's much tidier than Illidan's storage locker.

CRYSTALSONG PORTAL.name: Crystalsong Portal
CRYSTALSONG PORTAL.flavorText: Experience the draw of the wild!

FIRE PLUME'S HEART.name: Fire Plume's Heart
FIRE PLUME'S HEART.flavorText: Why does an active volcano need to be defended? To save its ash.

RECRUITER.name: Recruiter
RECRUITER.flavorText: Join the Argent Crusade! We have attractive tabards and you get to carry really nice swords!

WORGEN GREASER.name: Worgen Greaser
WORGEN GREASER.flavorText: Hair products are 79% of his monthly budget.

SHIELD BATTERY.name: Shield Battery
SHIELD BATTERY.flavorText: Hey Artanis, can I use your charger?

PORTAL KEEPER.name: Portal Keeper
PORTAL KEEPER.flavorText: No longer allowed to be “it” when playing demon tag.

TREASURE DISTRIBUTOR.name: Treasure Distributor
TREASURE DISTRIBUTOR.flavorText: As the illiterate pirates always say: There is no 'I' in 'piracy'.

SHELLSHIFTER.name: Shellshifter
SHELLSHIFTER.flavorText: Master of the Three Shell Monte.

PRIMALFIN TOTEM.name: Primalfin Totem
PRIMALFIN TOTEM.flavorText: Emits a sound only murlocs can hear, which is good because it’s REALLY annoying.

ARCANITE REAPER.name: Arcanite Reaper
ARCANITE REAPER.flavorText: No… actually you should fear the Reaper.

KAYN SUNFURY.name: Kayn Sunfury
KAYN SUNFURY.flavorText: "Armor and heals may slow my zeal, but fel and glaives excite me!"

LOKHOLAR THE ICE LORD.name: Lokholar the Ice Lord
LOKHOLAR THE ICE LORD.flavorText: Suddenly the names of Iceblood Tower and Iceblood Garrison make a lot more sense.

DIGGING STRAIGHT DOWN.name: Digging Straight Down
DIGGING STRAIGHT DOWN.flavorText: You only make this mistake once.

COLDTOOTH YETI.name: Coldtooth Yeti
COLDTOOTH YETI.flavorText: Its arrival heralds the Brain Freeze Yeti.

MARK OF NATURE.name: Mark of Nature
MARK OF NATURE.flavorText: Druids call it the "Mark of Nature." Everyone else calls it "needing a bath."

GRIEVOUS BITE.name: Grievous Bite
GRIEVOUS BITE.flavorText: Ooh. I'll have a bite of this, and of this, and of this...

STEWARD OF DARKSHIRE.name: Steward of Darkshire
STEWARD OF DARKSHIRE.flavorText: Turns out divine shields are way cheaper if you buy in bulk.

MURLOC GROWFIN.name: Murloc Growfin
MURLOC GROWFIN.flavorText: Grows up to 8x its size! Just add water!

OAKEN SUMMONS.name: Oaken Summons
OAKEN SUMMONS.flavorText: The Guild used oak trees until they all turned to ash.

CRYSTAL CLUSTER.name: Crystal Cluster
CRYSTAL CLUSTER.flavorText: And if you can't fit any of the Elementals… do better.

SINISTER SOULCAGE.name: Sinister Soulcage
SINISTER SOULCAGE.flavorText: Also a pretty neat night light!

HOGGER, DOOM OF ELWYNN.name: Hogger, Doom of Elwynn
HOGGER, DOOM OF ELWYNN.flavorText: When C'thun went to sleep, he checked under his bed for Hogger.

CARNIVOROUS CUBICLE.name: Carnivorous Cubicle
CARNIVOROUS CUBICLE.flavorText: Hey, no eating at your desk!

ROLLING STONE.name: Rolling Stone
ROLLING STONE.flavorText: Sadly, the mariachi band it used to play in gathers no más.

SELF-SHARPENING SWORD.name: Self-Sharpening Sword
SELF-SHARPENING SWORD.flavorText: You no longer have to bring a stack of 2 swords to a test!

RHYTHM AND ROOTS.name: Rhythm and Roots
RHYTHM AND ROOTS.flavorText: For Zok's latest song, he decided to go back to his roots. Like the ones on a tree. Tree roots.

HALF-TIME SCAVENGER.name: Half-Time Scavenger
HALF-TIME SCAVENGER.flavorText: One player's trash is another's “Best In Slot”.

THE NAMELESS ONE.name: The Nameless One
THE NAMELESS ONE.flavorText: Used to be called " , the Nameless," but everyone got confused.

SHADOWED SPIRIT.name: Shadowed Spirit
SHADOWED SPIRIT.flavorText: They can't all be grim grinning ghosts.

BONECHEWER BRAWLER.name: Bonechewer Brawler
BONECHEWER BRAWLER.flavorText: When you get this swole, arrows are basically free acupuncture.

CLEAN THE SCENE.name: Clean the Scene
CLEAN THE SCENE.flavorText: Not even the holy Light can get anima out of white silk.

CONSTRUCT QUARTER.name: Construct Quarter
CONSTRUCT QUARTER.flavorText: It's not alive! IT'S NOT ALIIIIIVE!!!

SAXOPHONE SOLOIST.name: Saxophone Soloist
SAXOPHONE SOLOIST.flavorText: He used to play to crowds of adoring Murlocs, but 20 years later all that's left is gigs at secluded clubs and regrets. Where did all the time go? His dreams of fame and fortune, snuffed out like the flame of a small candle in a dimly lit bar. Nothing but smoke in the wind.

TALENTED ARCANIST.name: Talented Arcanist
TALENTED ARCANIST.flavorText: "Ey mon, you don't get this good just on raw talent ... but it helps."

KARGATH BLADEFIST.name: Kargath Bladefist
KARGATH BLADEFIST.flavorText: He rules the Shattered Hand orc clan with an iron... bladefist.

BACKFIRE.name: Backfire
BACKFIRE.flavorText: "That's the last time I let an imp spit gasoline into my car."

ANIMATE DEAD.name: Animate Dead
ANIMATE DEAD.flavorText: In the old days they used to animate the dead one bone at a time... it's all done by computer now.

VILE APOTHECARY.name: Vile Apothecary
VILE APOTHECARY.flavorText: When he's feeling extra malicious, he uses the licorice-flavored one.

FORBIDDEN RITUAL.name: Forbidden Ritual
FORBIDDEN RITUAL.flavorText: Actually, C'Thun gives his full support for this ritual.

ANCHORED TOTEM.name: Anchored Totem
ANCHORED TOTEM.flavorText: The Naga devised the perfect retaliation to any pirates dropping anchor in their domain: vandalism.

STARFALL.name: Starfall
STARFALL.flavorText: Is the sky falling? Yes. Yes it is.

SPURFANG.name: Spurfang
SPURFANG.flavorText: He's always smiling… Not by choice, but because it hurts to close his mouth.

PETAL PEDDLER.name: Petal Peddler
PETAL PEDDLER.flavorText: The Emerald Nightmare might actually be a good thing for her business.

LEECHING POISON.name: Leeching Poison
LEECHING POISON.flavorText: No actual leeches were harmed in the creation of this card.

IMP SWARM (RANK 1).name: Imp Swarm (Rank 1)
IMP SWARM (RANK 1).flavorText: Not a cauldron, or a mischief, or a cackle, but a swarm.

PATIENT ASSASSIN.name: Patient Assassin
PATIENT ASSASSIN.flavorText: He’s not really that patient. It just takes a while for someone to walk by that he can actually reach.

STEAM GUARDIAN.name: Steam Guardian
STEAM GUARDIAN.flavorText: Its boiling steam and erupting magma serve as a pretty good form of 2-Factor Authentication.

ARKONITE REVELATION.name: Arkonite Revelation
ARKONITE REVELATION.flavorText: And if it's a rkonite, revel in it.

ANGRY CHICKEN.name: Angry Chicken
ANGRY CHICKEN.flavorText: There is no beast more frightening (or ridiculous) than a fully enraged chicken.

INFERNAL STAPLER.name: Infernal Stapler
INFERNAL STAPLER.flavorText: Excuse me, I believe you have my stapler…

MECHANICAL WHELP.name: Mechanical Whelp
MECHANICAL WHELP.flavorText: "Well if I didn't build the whelp and YOU didn't build the whelp…"

KEEN REFLEX.name: Keen Reflex
KEEN REFLEX.flavorText: All of Onyxia's whelps were no match for Kurtrus' backflip.

FLAME LANCE.name: Flame Lance
FLAME LANCE.flavorText: It's on the rack next to ice lance, acid lance, and English muffin lance.

FIERY WAR AXE.name: Fiery War Axe
FIERY WAR AXE.flavorText: During times of tranquility and harmony, this weapon was called by its less popular name, Chilly Peace Axe.

NERUBIAN FLYER.name: Nerubian Flyer
NERUBIAN FLYER.flavorText: Undead Air Miles only cover Northrend and the surrounding coast.

ANCESTRAL SPIRIT.name: Ancestral Spirit
ANCESTRAL SPIRIT.flavorText: It was just a flesh wound.

BOOMBOSS THO'GRUN.name: Boomboss Tho'grun
BOOMBOSS THO'GRUN.flavorText: Ever since the Bloodrock Company hired this guy, business has been booming!

SPIRIT OF THE TIGER.name: Spirit of the Tiger
SPIRIT OF THE TIGER.flavorText: Less of a cantrip and more of a cat-nip.

ONE-EYED CHEAT.name: One-eyed Cheat
ONE-EYED CHEAT.flavorText: When pirates say there is no "Eye" in "team," they are very literal about it.

RAZORPETAL LASHER.name: Razorpetal Lasher
RAZORPETAL LASHER.flavorText: The reason why there are no zombies in Un'goro.

AMPLIFIED ELEKK.name: Amplified Elekk
AMPLIFIED ELEKK.flavorText: Before this show can continue, we have to bass-boost the elephant in the room.

FELFUSED BATTERY.name: Felfused Battery
FELFUSED BATTERY.flavorText: Dirdra is a big believer in green energy.

SWORD OF JUSTICE.name: Sword of Justice
SWORD OF JUSTICE.flavorText: I dub you Sir Loin of Beef!

THE PRIMUS.name: The Primus
THE PRIMUS.flavorText: As there is a Pantheon of titans, so is there also a Pantheon of Death, comprised of powerful rulers in the Shadowlands.

SCALE REPLICA.name: Scale Replica
SCALE REPLICA.flavorText: Get it!?! It's because dragons have hides - commonly known as scales - and this is a model of a dragon on a smaller level, also known as a scale. IT'S THE SAME WORD!

HIGH PRIEST THEKAL.name: High Priest Thekal
HIGH PRIEST THEKAL.flavorText: "…and then I beat him with 1 Health!"

GOLD ROAD GRUNT.name: Gold Road Grunt
GOLD ROAD GRUNT.flavorText: No, no, no, Gold Roads are very different from Yellow Brick Roads.

DRAGONFIRE POTION.name: Dragonfire Potion
DRAGONFIRE POTION.flavorText: No one was brave enough to fire the dragon in person… so they made the potion do it.

DISGUISED WANDERER.name: Disguised Wanderer
DISGUISED WANDERER.flavorText: He wanders east... always into the east.

TAURAJO BRAVE.name: Taurajo Brave
TAURAJO BRAVE.flavorText: "He's brave, but splinters will make any Tauren cry."

BENEVOLENT DJINN.name: Benevolent Djinn
BENEVOLENT DJINN.flavorText: Wish 1: funnel cakes. Wish 2: funnel cakes. Wish 3: FUNNEL CAKES.

TUNNEL BLASTER.name: Tunnel Blaster
TUNNEL BLASTER.flavorText: And you always thought they wore the candles just for fun.

CORPSE RAISER.name: Corpse Raiser
CORPSE RAISER.flavorText: He was just minding his business, farming corpses, when you meddling adventurers came along.

FLESHSHAPER.name: Fleshshaper
FLESHSHAPER.flavorText: Even THIS is better than paper straws.

IMP KING RAFAAM.name: Imp King Rafaam
IMP KING RAFAAM.flavorText: Not even death can stop Rafaam from pursuing a life of crime.

FLAMECANNON.name: Flamecannon
FLAMECANNON.flavorText: Calling something a flamecannon really doesn't do much to distinguish it from other goblin devices.

LUNA'S POCKET GALAXY.name: Luna's Pocket Galaxy
LUNA'S POCKET GALAXY.flavorText: Luna became head of the astronomy department when her boss invented the Pocket Black Hole.

SOLAR ECLIPSE.name: Solar Eclipse
SOLAR ECLIPSE.flavorText: When the Moon is between the Sun and the Azeroth.

REMORSELESS WINTER.name: Remorseless Winter
REMORSELESS WINTER.flavorText: In the Badlands, this is a Rare.

NAGRAND SLAM.name: Nagrand Slam
NAGRAND SLAM.flavorText: Come on and slam, and welcome to Nagrand!

DOOMHAMMER.name: Doomhammer
DOOMHAMMER.flavorText: Orgrim Doomhammer gave this legendary weapon to Thrall. His name is a total coincidence.

BONE FLINGER.name: Bone Flinger
BONE FLINGER.flavorText: It’s the scourge bringing, plague slinging, bone flinging basher!

TOTALLY TOTEMS.name: Totally Totems
TOTALLY TOTEMS.flavorText: Hmph. Should've been Grace of Air Totem. Hmph.

DRAGON GOLEM.name: Dragon Golem
DRAGON GOLEM.flavorText: I have a Dragon, I have a Golem. UH! Dragon Golem!

YOGG-SARON, UNLEASHED.name: Yogg-Saron, Unleashed
YOGG-SARON, UNLEASHED.flavorText: Has been known to monologue before he strikes.

SKETCHY INFORMATION.name: Sketchy Information
SKETCHY INFORMATION.flavorText: "I trust the Forsaken as far as I can smell them. Which, I guess is actually pretty far."

CHORUS RIFF.name: Chorus Riff
CHORUS RIFF.flavorText: What do you mean, what do you mean, I SAY WHAT DO YOU MEEEEEAN, mean, mean, meaaaaaaan this chorus is repetitive?

NORDRASSIL DRUID.name: Nordrassil Druid
NORDRASSIL DRUID.flavorText: The World Tree Nordrassil provides life-giving energy to the world--and excellent mana savings.

BESTIAL WRATH.name: Bestial Wrath
BESTIAL WRATH.flavorText: The seething wrath is just beneath the surface. Beneath that is wild abandon, followed by slight annoyance.

SPLITTING SPACEROCK.name: Splitting Spacerock
SPLITTING SPACEROCK.flavorText: Space rock. *pew* Spa ce ro ck. *pew* S p a c e r o c k .

TIRION FORDRING.name: Tirion Fordring
TIRION FORDRING.flavorText: If you haven't heard the Tirion Fordring theme song, it's because it doesn't exist.

TINY KNIGHT OF EVIL.name: Tiny Knight of Evil
TINY KNIGHT OF EVIL.flavorText: "No, no, no. I asked for a tiny JESTER of evil."

TINKMASTER OVERSPARK.name: Tinkmaster Overspark
TINKMASTER OVERSPARK.flavorText: Tinkmaster Overspark nearly lost his Tinker's license after the Great Ironforge Squirrel Stampede of '09.

MOTHERSHIP.name: Mothership
MOTHERSHIP.flavorText: You talk to your mothership with that mouth!?

POWER OF THE WILD.name: Power of the Wild
POWER OF THE WILD.flavorText: Never look a panther in the eye. Or is it 'Always look a panther in the eye'? Well, it's one of those.

ANCIENT MYSTERIES.name: Ancient Mysteries
ANCIENT MYSTERIES.flavorText: I'm not saying it was aliens, but it was TOTALLY aliens!

SHADOWCASTER.name: Shadowcaster
SHADOWCASTER.flavorText: I mean, it's not creepy if you ASK before you steal their shadow to make a small replica of them to keep on your shelf.

GRAVITY LAPSE.name: Gravity Lapse
GRAVITY LAPSE.flavorText: Did someone forget to pay the gravity bill?

COBALT GUARDIAN.name: Cobalt Guardian
COBALT GUARDIAN.flavorText: Guardians used to be built out of Adamantium, but production got moved to Gadgetzan and Cobalt was cheap.

WAKENER OF SOULS.name: Wakener of Souls
WAKENER OF SOULS.flavorText: The alarm again!? Wake me up in 5 more eternities.

ANIMAL COMPANION.name: Animal Companion
ANIMAL COMPANION.flavorText: You could summon Misha, Leokk, or Huffer! Huffer is more trouble than he's worth.

SHIMMERING SUNFISH.name: Shimmering Sunfish
SHIMMERING SUNFISH.flavorText: Just keep shimmering, just keep shimmering.

HAGATHA'S SCHEME.name: Hagatha's Scheme
HAGATHA'S SCHEME.flavorText: "All shall suffer!" "But Hagatha, those are your minions..." "I said ALL!!!"

TIME-LOST RAPTOR.name: Time-Lost Raptor
TIME-LOST RAPTOR.flavorText: Much of his time lost no-lifeing Diablo IV.

ELDRITCH HORROR.name: Eldritch Horror
ELDRITCH HORROR.flavorText: Often wonders what path his life might have taken if he wasn't named, you know, "Eldritch Horror".

PLAGIARIZARRR.name: Plagiarizarrr
PLAGIARIZARRR.flavorText: He's also working on his own Hearthstone expansion: Festival of Epics.

CURSED BLADE.name: Cursed Blade
CURSED BLADE.flavorText: The Curse is that you have to listen to "MMMBop" on repeat.

FURNACE FUEL.name: Furnace Fuel
FURNACE FUEL.flavorText: Remember Ultrasaur? This is him now. Feel old yet?

AL'AKIR THE WINDLORD.name: Al'Akir the Windlord
AL'AKIR THE WINDLORD.flavorText: He is the weakest of the four Elemental Lords. And the other three don't let him forget it.

BARAK KODOBANE.name: Barak Kodobane
BARAK KODOBANE.flavorText: They say he's a pro at horseback archery.

E.T.C., BAND MANAGER.name: E.T.C., Band Manager
E.T.C., BAND MANAGER.flavorText: "This next band features the one and only M.C. Tech on the drums, the fungal king of the keyboard Loatheb, and the showstopping vocal chops of Spellbreaker!"

KNIFE JUGGLER.name: Knife Juggler
KNIFE JUGGLER.flavorText: Ambitious Knife Jugglers sometimes graduate to Bomb Jugglers. They never last long enough to make it onto a card though.

LOAN SHARK.name: Loan Shark
LOAN SHARK.flavorText: Pay up or you'll be swimming with the fishes.

GRAVEYARD SHIFT.name: Graveyard Shift
GRAVEYARD SHIFT.flavorText: "Why are we even open at night? This place is dead!"

WHIRLING ZAP-O-MATIC.name: Whirling Zap-o-matic
WHIRLING ZAP-O-MATIC.flavorText: If you pay a little extra, you can get it in "candy-apple red."

HIDDEN OBJECTS.name: Hidden Objects
HIDDEN OBJECTS.flavorText: There are 99 gnomes in this picture. Can YOU find them all?

ACHERUS VETERAN.name: Acherus Veteran
ACHERUS VETERAN.flavorText: This is my Runeblade. There are many like it but this one is mine.

YOUNG DRAGONHAWK.name: Young Dragonhawk
YOUNG DRAGONHAWK.flavorText: They were the inspiration for the championship Taurenball team: The Dragonhawks.

WINDFURY HARPY.name: Windfury Harpy
WINDFURY HARPY.flavorText: Harpies are not pleasant sounding. That's the nicest I can put it.

HOLY SPRINGWATER.name: Holy Springwater
HOLY SPRINGWATER.flavorText: Issa bah oh auh woh ah!

NECROTIC MORTICIAN.name: Necrotic Mortician
NECROTIC MORTICIAN.flavorText: Her hair, just like her name, is full of 'tic's.

VILEFIEND TRAINER.name: Vilefiend Trainer
VILEFIEND TRAINER.flavorText: My Vilefiend Trainers give me a much better sprint than my Air Gul'dans.

RUNED ORB.name: Runed Orb
RUNED ORB.flavorText: The most dangerous Winter Veil ornament.

DREAD DESERTER.name: Dread Deserter
DREAD DESERTER.flavorText: "I uh... need to go walk my uh… fish."

LAY DOWN THE LAW.name: Lay Down the Law
LAY DOWN THE LAW.flavorText: The official term for "Because I said so!".

SHIELD BLOCK.name: Shield Block
SHIELD BLOCK.flavorText: Shields were invented because Face Block is USELESS.

LOTUS AGENTS.name: Lotus Agents
LOTUS AGENTS.flavorText: Mostly, they stand around and look cool.

ROCKBITER WEAPON.name: Rockbiter Weapon
ROCKBITER WEAPON.flavorText: This would be real handy if your enemy is made of rock.

CHARGED DEVILSAUR.name: Charged Devilsaur
CHARGED DEVILSAUR.flavorText: What happens when a dinosaur mixes soda and pop rocks.

DEFEND THE DWARVEN DISTRICT.name: Defend the Dwarven District
DEFEND THE DWARVEN DISTRICT.flavorText: Don't shoot until you see the purples of their eyes.

SOUTHSEA CAPTAIN.name: Southsea Captain
SOUTHSEA CAPTAIN.flavorText: When he saves enough plunder, he's going to commission an enormous captain's hat. He has hat envy.

RAID THE SKY TEMPLE.name: Raid the Sky Temple
RAID THE SKY TEMPLE.flavorText: "Why can't I hold all these scrolls?"

MANA GEODE.name: Mana Geode
MANA GEODE.flavorText: Gadgetzan, where even the pet rocks have pet rocks.

TIDAL REVENANT.name: Tidal Revenant
TIDAL REVENANT.flavorText: A big minion that clears the board and gains Armor? Wow, Warrior is really in their element now.

TAUREN WARRIOR.name: Tauren Warrior
TAUREN WARRIOR.flavorText: Tauren Warrior: Champion of Mulgore, Slayer of Quilboar, Rider of Thunderbluff Elevators.

MANUFACTURING ERROR.name: Manufacturing Error
MANUFACTURING ERROR.flavorText: You thought the 9-piece puzzle would be easy, didn't you?

SPEAKER GIDRA.name: Speaker Gidra
SPEAKER GIDRA.flavorText: If a teacher lectures in a forest, does she even make a sound?

MALYGOS.name: Malygos
MALYGOS.flavorText: Malygos hates it when mortals use magic. He gets so mad!

LIGHTSHOWER ELEMENTAL.name: Lightshower Elemental
LIGHTSHOWER ELEMENTAL.flavorText: The forecast calls for light showers, but you won’t need an umbrella.

FELFIRE THRUSTERS.name: Felfire Thrusters
FELFIRE THRUSTERS.flavorText: The coolness factor of a fire decal is universal.

GLACIAL ADVANCE.name: Glacial Advance
GLACIAL ADVANCE.flavorText: You just wait, I'll get there in 10 years and then you'll be sorry.

DEATH'S HEAD CULTIST.name: Death's Head Cultist
DEATH'S HEAD CULTIST.flavorText: Nothing can stop death. Except a Taunt. With Healing.

CAVERN SHINYFINDER.name: Cavern Shinyfinder
CAVERN SHINYFINDER.flavorText: They call her the candled vandal.

ORIGAMI DRAGON.name: Origami Dragon
ORIGAMI DRAGON.flavorText: The fire will give you a papercut, which CAN burn. Does that count?

ANUBISATH WARBRINGER.name: Anubisath Warbringer
ANUBISATH WARBRINGER.flavorText: Some dogs will bring you a bone or a squeaky toy. This one brings war!

NETHRANDAMUS.name: Nethrandamus
NETHRANDAMUS.flavorText: Missed the big descent with the other dragons. But better late and nether!

voicelines.attack:
https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/0/01/VO_BT_481_Male_Netherdrake_Play_02.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_BT_481_Male_Netherdrake_Play_02.wav Gaze into the nether! Find your power!
  • ▶️ Nethrandamus_Play_Stinger.wav <music stinger>

BURDEN OF PRIDE.name: Burden of Pride
BURDEN OF PRIDE.flavorText: A group of burdens is called a pride.

SKY MOTHER AVIANA.name: Sky Mother Aviana
SKY MOTHER AVIANA.flavorText: It's a bird! It's a plane! It's 10 copies of Leeroy Jenkins!

HORDE OPERATIVE.name: Horde Operative
HORDE OPERATIVE.flavorText: "We all have our secrets. I mean, your secrets."

ALEXSTRASZA'S CHAMPION.name: Alexstrasza's Champion
ALEXSTRASZA'S CHAMPION.flavorText: "Put more spikes on her. No, more spikes. What part of 'more spikes' do you not understand? MORE SPIKES!" - Alexstrasza

voicelines.play: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/7/7b/VO_AT_071_PLAY_01.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_071_PLAY_01.wav

voicelines.death: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/9/9e/VO_AT_071_DEATH_03.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_071_DEATH_03.wav <death sound>

SHADOW ESSENCE.name: Shadow Essence
SHADOW ESSENCE.flavorText: Difficult to bottle up and sell. But it packs a punch.

NOXIOUS INFILTRATOR.name: Noxious Infiltrator
NOXIOUS INFILTRATOR.flavorText: Noxious, but not toxic - he's very polite!

COMMANDER ULTHOK.name: Commander Ulthok
COMMANDER ULTHOK.flavorText: He likes to spend his free time in his garden, growing Bloodradish, Bloodcabbage, and his favorite, Bloodbloom.

LOST EXARCH.name: Lost Exarch
LOST EXARCH.flavorText: She resisted the temptation of the Burning Legion's power only to fall victim to the Scourge.

DOOMSAYER.name: Doomsayer
DOOMSAYER.flavorText: He's almost been right so many times. He was sure it was coming during the Cataclysm.

TORTOLLAN PRIMALIST.name: Tortollan Primalist
TORTOLLAN PRIMALIST.flavorText: I see pizza in my future.

UNTAMED BEASTMASTER.name: Untamed Beastmaster
UNTAMED BEASTMASTER.flavorText: All it takes is a tummy rub.

TORGHAST CUSTODIAN.name: Torghast Custodian
TORGHAST CUSTODIAN.flavorText: Why is it a common? Well we couldn't make it a LEGendary minion!

PSYCHE SPLIT.name: Psyche Split
PSYCHE SPLIT.flavorText: This is how the arakkoa make friends.

SHADOW SENSEI.name: Shadow Sensei
SHADOW SENSEI.flavorText: He used to be Aya's tutor, but she fired him for bugging her too much.

MASTER JOUSTER.name: Master Jouster
MASTER JOUSTER.flavorText: Needs just a few more ratings points to become Grandmaster Jouster.

voicelines.play: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/a/ac/VO_AT_112_PLAY_01.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_112_PLAY_01.wav
voicelines.attack: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/3/37/VO_AT_112_ATTACK_03.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_112_ATTACK_03.wav Prepare to lose!
voicelines.death: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/0/0a/VO_AT_112_DEATH_04.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_112_DEATH_04.wav Inconceivable!

BOMB LOBBER.name: Bomb Lobber
BOMB LOBBER.flavorText: He lobbies Orgrimmar daily on behalf of bombs.

WORKSHOP MISHAP.name: Workshop Mishap
WORKSHOP MISHAP.flavorText: IT HAS BEEN DAYS SINCE LAST ACCIDENT.

SHADO-PAN RIDER.name: Shado-Pan Rider
SHADO-PAN RIDER.flavorText: He needed a break after that business in the Vale of Eternal Blossoms. Naturally, he chose to spend his vacation in an icy snowscape killing monsters.

voicelines.play: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/c/c8/VO_AT_028_PLAY_01.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_028_PLAY_01.wav
voicelines.attack: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/d/d6/VO_AT_028_ATTACK_02.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_028_ATTACK_02.wav Shadow strike!
voicelines.death: https://hearthstone.wiki.gg/images/6/66/VO_AT_028_DEATH_03.wav" type="audio/wav" />Link▶️ VO_AT_028_DEATH_03.wav <death sound>

ROCKET HOPPER.name: Rocket Hopper
ROCKET HOPPER.flavorText: Are y'all gonna ask for THIS one to be orange too!?

GLOWROOT LURE.name: Glowroot Lure
GLOWROOT LURE.flavorText: You'd think this is a creation of the Emerald Nightmare, but you would be wrong.

ALWAYS A BIGGER JORMUNGAR.name: Always a Bigger Jormungar
ALWAYS A BIGGER JORMUNGAR.flavorText: I saw it! It's big, scary, and blue!
